@node Besoins "Requirements"

	Well, not much. I didn't do a lot of tests, but I think SmallGrabber will need the Amiga OS 2.04 to work properly. It also needs the reqtools lib (copyrights Nico François), that I hope you already have.

				@{"Main Page" LINK MAIN}
@endnode
@node "Life Team"

	The Life Team is a small french programming group, which has for main goal to distribute freeware proggyes, Shareware's (and why not commercial's ;-) on Amiga. Our programs are all made with the powerfull Blitz Basic 2 by Acid Software. Our second goal is to make Blitz wellknown (mainly in France), because it is probably one of the best languages around. 

@{b}Life Team progs :@{ub}

@{b}_ W-Anim :@{ub} an IFF anim in window viewer. It has lots of functions (frame rate, palette 
choose ...).

@{b}_ Insulte :@{ub} a program that insults you ( french only at the moment :-( ) !!!

@{b}_ LTAssign :@{ub} an AppIcon that assigns files dropped on it.

@{b}_ Searcher :@{ub} a powerfull file finder with a superb GUI.

@{b}_ SmallPlayer :@{ub} a protracker format module player. 

@{b}_ AppSize :@{ub} a directory sizer.

@{b}_ IRT :@{ub} Icon Replacement Tool, an AppWindow that allows you to easily change your icons.

@{b}_ IconPlayer :@{ub} An AppIcon to play protracker modules files.

You can find all those programms on your favourite aminet site or at your DP distributor.

				        @{"Author" LINK Auteur}.

					@{"Main Page" LINK MAIN}
@endnode
