@node SmallGrabber

	Once you launched SmallGrabber by clicking on its icon, you will have a few options :

@{b}_ Save Path :@{ub} specify the path where you want SGrabber to save the pictures in.

@{b}_ Save Name :@{ub} the name which will be given to youur grabbed screen (SmallGrabIFF will be SmallGrabIFF1, SmallGrabIFF2, SmallGrabIFF3 ...)

@{b}_ Grabbing Hotkey :@{ub} the hotkey that will save your screen

@{b}_ Exit Hotkey :@{ub} the hotkey that make you exit SmallGrabber ;-)

You can use the Hotkeys defined to grab screens or to exit SmallGrabber. Be carefull : if you are running a 256 colors Hires WorkBench, it would take SmallGrabber quite a long time (about 30 s) to save your screen due to the lot of operations SmallGrabber has to do to have the exact palette and resolution. After that, you can rule SmallGrabber with the Exchange program, which is in you SYS:Tools/Commodities directory. 

					@{"Main Page" LINK MAIN}
@endnode
@node Futur "SmallGrabber's Future"

	Well, I'll try to fix the latest bugs, to localize SG in different languages, and to have an option "Save Active Window Only". Stay tuned !

					@{"Main Page" LINK MAIN}
@endnode
